race.comment: Easy to make a case for any of these. CREPE MYRTLE (3) gets the verdict after winning with a bit to spare last time out over this distance at Gosford. Lightly raced four-year-old with more to offer at just the third run of the campaign. SWORDPLAY (11) led from the get-go and demolished her rivals when fresh from a five-month spell recently over 900m at Newcastle. Needs to sustain that effort for an extra furlong and meets a deeper field but this lightly raced filly has a stack of upside. ZOUNAKA (7) disappointed at Rosehill a week ago but can do better back to this journey with blinkers applied for the first time. Nice inclusion at big odds. NINETTE (10) led and gave a great sight before finding a couple better first-up over this trip at Rosehill. Cruised to victory second-up last prep so she should come on from that run. UNITED STATES (6) resumes. Didn't measure up in a couple of Group 2 races last time in work but is a genuine hope kicking off in this grade.
